This paper is primarily focused on video understanding and temporal modeling, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper also discusses the need for better training and benchmarking methods, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the human annotation experiment used in the paper could involve natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
